\n   - Flow control (connection + per-stream)\n\n2. **Security (Phase 5)**\n   - AEAD encryption (AES-256-GCM, ChaCha20-Poly1305)\n   - HKDF key derivation\n   - X25519 key exchange\n   - Header protection\n   - Secure memory wiping\n\n3. **Advanced Features (Phase 6)**\n   - 0-RTT resumption with session tickets\n   - Connection migration (IP/port changes)\n   - Replay attack protection (strike register)\n   - Retry tokens for address validation\n\n4. **Performance (Phase 7)**\n   - BBR congestion control (full v1 implementation)\n   - Packet pacing\n   - Delivery rate estimation\n   - Windowed max/min filters\n\n5. **Built-in Features (Phase 8)**\n   - Heartbeat/keep-alive\n   - Auto-reconnect (client-side)\n   - Per-stream rate limiting\n   - Backpressure callbacks\n\n6. **Observability (Recent)**\n   - Quill-based structured logging (C++ wrapper)\n   - Flight recorder (circular buffer for debugging)\n   - Error tracking system\n   - DoS rate limiting\n\n---\n\n### **Code Quality & Security**\n\n#### **Security Audit Status** (from SECURITY_AUDIT.md)\n- ✅ **Input validation**: All packet/frame parsers fuzzed\n- ✅ **Crypto security**: Constant-time comparisons, nonce uniqueness\n- ✅ **DoS protection**: Rate limiting, connection limits, amplification protection\n- ✅ **Memory safety**: ASAN/UBSAN/MSAN tested\n- ✅ **State machine validation**: All transitions verified\n\n#### **Testing Infrastructure**\n- **Unit tests**: 20+ test files covering all components\n- **Fuzz tests**: Frame and packet parsers\n- **Integration tests**: UDP echo server\n- **Examples**: TCP-like and UDP-like protocol demos\n\n---\n\n### **Technical Highlights**\n\n#### **1. Stream Types**\n```c\nNXP_STREAM_RELIABLE  // TCP-like: ordered, reliable\nNXP_STREAM_FAST      // UDP-like: unordered, unreliable\nNXP_STREAM_MEDIA     // Partially reliable (drop old data)\nNXP_STREAM_FILE      // Bulk transfer optimized\n```\n\n#### **2. Crypto Implementation**\n- Initial keys derived from connection ID 