ol (connection + per-stream)\n\n2. **Security (Phase 5)**\n   - AEAD encryption (AES-256-GCM, ChaCha20-Poly1305)\n   - HKDF key derivation\n   - X25519 key exchange\n   - Header protection\n   - Secure memory wiping\n\n3. **Advanced Features (Phase 6)**\n   - 0-RTT resumption with session tickets\n   - Connection migration (IP/port changes)\n   - Replay attack protection (strike register)\n   - Retry tokens for address validation\n\n4. **Performance (Phase 7)**\n   - BBR congestion control (full v1 implementation)\n   - Packet pacing\n   - Delivery rate estimation\n   - Windowed max/min filters\n\n5. **Built-in Features (Phase 8)**\n   - Heartbeat/keep-alive\n   - Auto-reconnect (client-side)\n   - Per-stream rate limiting\n   - Backpressure callbacks\n\n6. **Observability (Recent)**\n   - Quill-based structured logging (C++ wrapper)\n   - Flight recorder (circular buffer for debugging)\n   - Error tracking system\n   - DoS rate limiting\n\n---\n\n### **Code Quality & Security**\n\n#### **Security Audit Status** (from SECURITY_AUDIT.md)\n- ✅ **Input validation**: All packet/frame parsers fuzzed\n- ✅ **Crypto security**: Constant-time comparisons, nonce uniqueness\n- ✅ **DoS protection**: Rate limiting, connection limits, amplification protection\n- ✅ **Memory safety**: ASAN/UBSAN/MSAN tested\n- ✅ **State machine validation**: All transitions verified\n\n#### **Testing Infrastructure**\n- **Unit tests**: 20+ test files covering all components\n- **Fuzz tests**: Frame and packet parsers\n- **Integration tests**: UDP echo server\n- **Examples**: TCP-like and UDP-like protocol demos\n\n---\n\n### **Technical Highlights**\n\n#### **1. Stream Types**\n```c\nNXP_STREAM_RELIABLE  // TCP-like: ordered, reliable\nNXP_STREAM_FAST      // UDP-like: unordered, unreliable\nNXP_STREAM_MEDIA     // Partially reliable (drop old data)\nNXP_STREAM_FILE      // Bulk transfer optimized\n```\n\n#### **2. Crypto Implementation**\n- Initial keys derived from connection ID (like QUIC)\n- Full handshake with X25519 ECDH\n- Separate packet number spaces (Initial, Handshake, Application)\n- Header protection to prevent ossification\n\n#### **3. BBR Congestion Control**\n- Bandwidth probing with windowed max filter\n- RTT tracking with min filter\n- 4 states: STARTUP → DRAIN → PROBE_BW ↔ PROBE_RTT\n- Pacing to avoid bursts\n\n#### **4. Memory Management**\n- Arena allocator for temporary allocations\n- Pool allocator for fixed-size objects\n- Slab allocator for packet buffers\n- Ring buffers for stream data\n\n---\n\n### **Platform Support**\n\n**Current:**\n- ✅ Linux (epoll event loop)\n- ✅ POSIX sockets, threads, time\n\n**Planned:**\n- ⏳ Windows (IOCP)\n- ⏳ macOS (kqueue)\n- ⏳ io_uring (Linux high-performance)\n\n---\n\n### **Build System**\n- **CMake 3.25+** with modern targets\n- **C23** for core, **C++** for logging (Quill)\n- **OpenSSL 3.0+** required\n- Optional: ASAN, UBSAN, TSAN, fuzzing\n- Generates both shared (`.so`) and static (`.a`) libraries\n\n---\n\n### **Production Readiness**\n\n**Status: 42% Complete (5/12 milestones)**\n\n**Remaining Work:**\n1. **Observability** (Critical) - Metrics API, debug tools\n2. **Performance** (High) - Profiling, benchmarks vs QUIC/TCP\n3. **API Stability** (High) - Finalize public API, ABI versioning\n4. **Testing** (High) - Stress tests (10K+ connections, 24h runs)\n5. **Documentation** (Medium) - API reference, architecture docs\n\n**Estimated Timeline:**\n- MVP (v1.0): 1 week\n- Production (v1.1): 2 weeks\n- Enterprise (v2.0): 1 month\n\n---\n\n### **Code Statistics**\n\n```\nSource Files:     ~80 files\nLines of Code:    ~15,000 LOC (estimated)\nLanguages:        C (95%), C++ (5% - logging)\nDependencies:     OpenSSL 3.x, Quill (optional)\nTest Coverage:    Unit + Integration + Fuzz\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Key Strengths**\n\n1. **Clean Architecture**: Sans-I/O design makes testing easy\n2. **Security**: Comprehensive audit completed, crypto properly implemented\n3. **Performance**: BBR + pacing + zero-copy paths\n4. **Flexibility**: 4 stream types cover different use cases\n5. **Modern C**: Uses C23 features, strict standards compliance\n\n### **Areas for Improvement**\n\n1. **Documentation**: Needs API reference and architecture docs\n2. **Benchmarks**: No performance comparison data yet\n3. **Multi-platform**: Only Linux fully supported\n4. **Metrics**: No Prometheus/observability integration\n5. **Stress Testing**: Needs long-running stability tests\n\n---\n\n### **Use Cases**\n\nThis protocol is suitable for:\n- **Gaming**: Low-latency with FAST streams\n- **Video Streaming**: MEDIA streams with partial reliability\n- **File Transfer**: FILE streams with bulk optimization\n- **RPC/Microservices**: RELIABLE streams like TCP\n- **IoT**: Connection migration for mobile devices\n\n---\n\nThis is a **well-architected, security-focused transport protocol** that's about 40% away from production readiness. The core protocol implementation is solid, but needs observability, performance validation, and documentation to be production-ready.\n[Tool uses: none]",
